            <p>LAPPESC is a research group coordinated by <a href="http://www.ime.usp.br/~gerosa" class="left" target=_blank>prof. Marco Aur&eacute;lio Gerosa</a>, located at the <a href="http://www.ime.usp.br/dcc" target=_blank>Computer Science Department</a> of the <a href="http://www.ime.usp.br" target=_blank>Math and Statistics Institute</a>, <a href="http://www.usp.br" target=_blank>University of S&atilde;o Paulo</a>, Brazil. The objective of the group is to investigate the areas of Software Engineering and Collaborative Systems (Computer Supported Cooperative Work - CSCW) and their intersections. The group adopts an approach based on tool support for collaborative analysis, design, and development of software.</p>           

